---
import Layout from '../components/layout.astro';
---

<style>
.wrapper {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.features {
  display: grid;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin: 2rem 0;
}

.feature {
  background: var(--white);
  border: 1px solid var(--lightBorder);
  border-radius: var(--card-radius);
  padding: 1.5rem;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgb(14 30 37 / 12%);
}

.feature h3 {
  color: var(--heading);
  margin-top: 0;
}

.feature p {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}
</style>

<Layout
  title="Netlify Projects"
  description="Organize your sites, manage environments, and collaborate with your team all from a unified dashboard."
>
  <main>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <h2>Manage everything from one place</h2>
      <p>
        Netlify Projects help you organize and manage your sites with powerful
        features designed for modern web development workflows.
      </p>

      <div class="features">
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Unified Dashboard</h3>
          <p>
            View all your sites, deployments, and builds in one central location.
            Track performance metrics and deployment history across all your projects.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Environment Management</h3>
          <p>
            Easily manage production, staging, and development environments.
            Configure environment variables, build settings, and deploy contexts
            for each environment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Team Collaboration</h3>
          <p>
            Invite team members, set permissions, and collaborate seamlessly.
            Share deploy previews, review changes, and ship with confidence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Build Monitoring</h3>
          <p>
            Monitor build times, track deployment success rates, and get
            notifications when something goes wrong. Keep your team informed
            and productive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Get started with Projects</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          Visit
          <a href="https://app.netlify.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            app.netlify.com
          </a>
          and sign in to your account.
        </li>
        <li>
          Click "Add new site" to create a new project or select an existing
          site from your dashboard.
        </li>
        <li>
          Configure your project settings, environment variables, and build
          commands.
        </li>
        <li>
          Invite team members and set up permissions under the "Site settings"
          → "Team and access" section.
        </li>
        <li>
          Deploy your site and manage all aspects from the unified project
          dashboard.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p>
        <a href="https://docs.netlify.com/site-deploys/overview/">
          Learn about Netlify Projects in the docs.
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
